<DOC><DOCNO> AP890521-0080 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-21-89 2200EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Philippines-Fire     05-21 0152</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Philippines-Fire,0156</SECOND><HEAD>Fire Kills 14 in Manila</HEAD><DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Fourteen people, including a1-year-old girl, were killed when fire swept through a crowdedManila neighborhood early Monday, police said.   Lt. Honorato Manuel, chief of the Manila police arson division,said the fire began in the stairs of an old two-story wooden housein the Santa Ana district, where four families were renting rooms.   Two of the families escaped through the back stairs but theothers were trapped in their rooms, which had iron bars in thewindows, Manuel said. Among those killed were seven children and a70-year-old man, he added.   ``Witnesses said the victims were waving and calling for help,but neighbors could not go near because it was already very hot andthey did not know how to save the people trapped inside,'' Manuelsaid.   The fire lasted for 45 minutes and razed 10 houses, Manuel said.</TEXT></DOC>